  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis is a slightly open-ended issue for improving the interaction of the state advance timer with `tree-states`. Some improvements that could be made include:\r\n\r\n1. Advancing multiple states into the new epoch, e.g. the head (at slot 31) and the parent of the head (at slot 30). This could help us process re-orging blocks faster by avoiding the epoch-transition.\r\n2. Advancing multiple slots at a time. This could also help with processing block around epoch boundaries if there is a skipped slot at the boundary, e.g. slot 31 is missed. Presently the state advance timer would only advance the head (e.g. at slot 30) by one slot, meaning that the epoch transition would be computed only once the block arrives.\r\n",
